  <text>
      <body>
        
     
      <div xml:id="Poem32"> 
              <interpGrp type="poembox">
                <interp ana="#form" type="free"></interp>
                <interp ana="#tone" type="sad"></interp>
                <interp ana="#topic" type="death"></interp>
              </interpGrp>
             <lg> 
               <l>After the blast of lightning from the east,</l>
               <l>The flourish of loud clouds, the Chariot throne,</l> 
               <l>After the drums of time have rolled and ceased</l>
               <l>And from the bronze west long retreat is blown,</l>
          <l> </l>
               <l>Shall Life renew these bodies? Of a truth</l>
               <l>All death will he annul, all tears assuage?</l>
               <l>Or fill these void veins full again with youth</l>
               <l>And wash with an immortal water age?</l>
          <l> </l>
               <l>When I do ask white Age, he saith not so,—</l>
               <l>“My head hangs weighted with snow.”</l>
               <l>And when I hearken to the Earth she saith</l>
               <l>“My fiery heart sinks aching. It is death.</l>
               <l>Mine ancient scars shall not be glorified</l>
               <l>Nor my titanic tears the seas be dried.”</l>
                 
